WEBVTT

00:17.640 --> 00:18.920
<i> The universe</i>…

00:20.160 --> 00:22.000
…<i>has provided our planet</i>

00:22.080 --> 00:25.200
<i>with all the ingredients</i>
<i>needed for life to emerge…</i>

00:26.240 --> 00:27.360
<i>…and flourish.</i>

00:29.520 --> 00:31.440
<i>The energy flowing through us</i>.

00:36.480 --> 00:38.520
<i>The daily rhythms we follow.</i>

00:41.400 --> 00:43.880
<i>The elements we are made of.</i>

00:47.280 --> 00:49.800
<i>But behind all these wonders</i>…

00:50.920 --> 00:52.840
…<i>lies a mysterious force</i>…

00:56.040 --> 00:58.520
…<i>that makes all of this possible.</i>

01:01.040 --> 01:01.920
<i>Gravity.</i>

01:08.600 --> 01:10.880
<i>It holds everything in place.</i>

01:15.760 --> 01:17.480
<i>It builds every star…</i>

01:20.600 --> 01:22.240
…<i>and shapes every planet.</i>

01:26.480 --> 01:28.600
<i>And guides every life.</i>

01:31.000 --> 01:33.400
<i>It's the ultimate force of attraction.</i>

01:35.480 --> 01:40.240
<i>So profound,</i>
<i>it will bring two young souls together</i>…

01:42.680 --> 01:45.880
<i>in their search for the perfect mate.</i>

02:13.720 --> 02:18.880
<i>In the Southern Ocean,</i>
<i>over 2,000 kilometers from Antarctica…</i>

02:21.680 --> 02:25.320
<i>…lies the windswept island</i>
<i>of South Georgia.</i>

02:29.920 --> 02:31.440
<i>Home to a colony</i>

02:32.840 --> 02:35.480
<i>of half a million king penguins.</i>

02:44.080 --> 02:47.080
<i>And it's a big day for two of them.</i>

02:52.600 --> 02:53.600
<i>New parents.</i>

02:59.040 --> 03:00.680
<i>For over 50 days…</i>

03:03.400 --> 03:07.480
<i>they've been taking turns</i>
<i>keeping their precious cargo safe</i>…

03:10.920 --> 03:12.240
<i>…and warm.</i>

03:14.920 --> 03:19.520
<i>And today, it's time</i>
<i>to welcome their baby son into the world.</i>

03:30.800 --> 03:31.680
<i>Little Rocky…</i>

03:35.080 --> 03:36.960
<i>meet big world.</i>

03:44.920 --> 03:47.440
<i>And on the other side of the island,</i>

03:48.320 --> 03:50.840
<i>another little chick is stepping out.</i>

03:54.720 --> 03:55.880
<i>A girl.</i>

03:57.200 --> 03:58.120
<i>Paloma.</i>

04:04.920 --> 04:09.240
<i>Rocky and Paloma don't know it yet,</i>
<i>but they are destined for each other.</i>

04:20.800 --> 04:24.120
<i>A force of attraction beyond their control</i>

04:25.520 --> 04:27.080
<i>will bring them together.</i>

04:35.920 --> 04:40.600
<i>This force not only hugs</i>
<i>Rocky and Paloma firmly to the ground…</i>

04:45.800 --> 04:48.680
…<i>it hugs our atmosphere to the planet.</i>

04:55.000 --> 04:57.000
<i>It keeps Earth orbiting the Sun…</i>

05:03.040 --> 05:08.160
<i>…the Sun rotating</i>
<i>around the center of our galaxy…</i>

05:09.920 --> 05:14.200
<i>…and galaxies dancing</i>
<i>and swirling around each other</i>

05:16.040 --> 05:18.280
<i>on the grandest of scales.</i>

05:21.720 --> 05:25.360
<i>Gravity holds all the pieces</i>
<i>of our universe together,</i>

05:26.600 --> 05:28.040
<i>connecting everything…</i>

05:31.600 --> 05:33.960
…<i>from the most distant star…</i>

05:41.640 --> 05:43.280
…<i>to the tiniest penguin.</i>

05:47.680 --> 05:52.400
<i>But Rocky and Paloma aren't thinking</i>
<i>about their place in the cosmos…</i>

05:56.440 --> 05:57.920
<i>…just their next meal.</i>

06:03.960 --> 06:07.160
<i>It's taking all the efforts</i>
<i>of their devoted parents</i>…

06:09.840 --> 06:12.400
<i>to feed their insatiable appetites.</i>

06:20.960 --> 06:22.080
<i>It's a thankless…</i>

06:25.520 --> 06:27.040
<i>and never-ending task.</i>

06:42.640 --> 06:47.120
<i>They're doing everything they can</i>
<i>to fatten their chicks in time for winter.</i>

06:50.040 --> 06:53.120
<i>Because as Rocky and Paloma</i>
<i>have been growing bigger…</i>

06:55.200 --> 06:58.440
<i>the days have been growing shorter.</i>

07:04.280 --> 07:07.000
<i>Food is becoming scarce.</i>

07:11.880 --> 07:14.160
<i>Their parents must leave the island…</i>

07:18.320 --> 07:21.480
<i>and travel hundreds of kilometers</i>
<i>out to sea</i>…

07:23.840 --> 07:25.120
<i>to hunt for food…</i>

07:27.160 --> 07:29.400
<i>leaving their precious chicks for months</i>

07:30.000 --> 07:32.360
<i>to fend for themselves.</i>

07:43.440 --> 07:46.040
<i>Paloma's cries go unanswered…</i>

07:48.200 --> 07:50.880
<i>as the first, loneliest night sets in.</i>

07:54.080 --> 07:56.880
<i>The darkest moment</i>
<i>in a penguin chick's life.</i>

08:05.200 --> 08:09.680
<i>But it's nothing compared</i>
<i>to our universe's darkest moments…</i>

08:12.800 --> 08:15.480
<i>because long before there was an Earth,</i>

08:17.280 --> 08:18.400
<i>a Sun,</i>

08:19.640 --> 08:20.880
<i>or stars…</i>

08:25.520 --> 08:27.400
<i>there was no light at all.</i>

08:37.200 --> 08:41.400
<i>The universe was just</i>
<i>a dark, dense web of gas.</i>

08:49.280 --> 08:53.280
<i>But here, gravity began to work its magic.</i>

08:56.600 --> 09:01.000
<i>From this gravity came everything.</i>

09:07.400 --> 09:09.520
<i>Parts of the web were pulled together</i>…

09:12.000 --> 09:13.640
<i>into clumps of matter</i>…

09:17.160 --> 09:19.640
<i>…that grew and grew…</i>

09:24.920 --> 09:29.840
<i>until they got so big,</i>
<i>they collapsed in on themselves…</i>

09:32.000 --> 09:33.480
<i>…bursting into life…</i>

09:38.680 --> 09:42.160
<i>…as the very first stars.</i>

09:50.800 --> 09:52.160
<i>Gravity kept working,</i>

09:52.880 --> 09:57.440
<i>sculpting the primordial web</i>
<i>into more and more stars…</i>

09:59.920 --> 10:02.000
<i>pulling them toward each other</i>

10:03.520 --> 10:06.280
<i>and spinning them into vast galaxies.</i>

10:13.800 --> 10:14.720
<i>From nothing,</i>

10:15.680 --> 10:19.400
<i>gravity shaped</i>
<i>an entire universe of possibility…</i>

10:22.760 --> 10:25.800
<i>that still speckles our night sky.</i>

10:35.800 --> 10:40.480
<i>But light from distant stars</i>
<i>won't keep penguin chicks warm.</i>

10:43.680 --> 10:45.280
<i>With their parents at sea,</i>

10:46.160 --> 10:49.120
<i>Rocky and Paloma are losing weight,</i>

10:50.560 --> 10:53.800
<i>becoming more and more vulnerable.</i>

11:10.400 --> 11:12.640
<i>The chicks only refuge from the cold</i>

11:13.480 --> 11:14.840
<i>is their fluffy down</i>

11:16.520 --> 11:17.440
<i>and each other.</i>

11:19.600 --> 11:23.680
<i>Their survival hinges</i>
<i>on a precise, elegant dance</i>

11:23.760 --> 11:25.480
<i>between one star</i>

11:26.320 --> 11:27.440
<i>and one planet,</i>

11:29.320 --> 11:34.080
<i>choreographed by gravity</i>
<i>over four and a half billion years ago.</i>

11:43.800 --> 11:47.720
<i>Out of the dust and gas left over</i>
<i>from the formation of the Sun…</i>

11:51.240 --> 11:54.160
<i>…gravity pulled bits and pieces</i>
<i>of rubble together…</i>

12:01.880 --> 12:05.080
<i>…molding them over time into a planet.</i>

12:15.920 --> 12:19.280
<i>It was unrecognizable</i>
<i>from the home we know now…</i>

12:21.720 --> 12:24.240
<i>but it had all the potential for life…</i>

12:28.040 --> 12:31.800
<i>bathed in the glow of our newborn Sun.</i>

12:36.520 --> 12:41.400
<i>That same Sun,</i>
<i>billions of years later, is now rising…</i>

12:45.640 --> 12:49.080
<i>…signaling to Rocky and Paloma's parents</i>,

12:49.960 --> 12:52.560
<i>it's time to return to South Georgia…</i>

12:56.960 --> 13:01.080
<i>with their bellies full of fish.</i>

13:08.600 --> 13:11.040
<i>As the sun warms the beaches,</i>

13:11.120 --> 13:14.480
<i>the island is transformed</i>
<i>into a haven once again.</i>

13:19.600 --> 13:22.880
<i>But making it to shore was the easy part.</i>

13:25.320 --> 13:28.480
<i>Rocky's parents</i>
<i>now have to find their baby</i>

13:29.240 --> 13:31.760
<i>amongst thousands of others.</i>

13:42.600 --> 13:47.560
<i>Up the coast, Paloma's parents</i>
<i>lock onto her special call</i>…

13:48.600 --> 13:50.720
…<i>and quickly find her in the crowd.</i>

13:58.240 --> 14:01.320
<i>And finally, Rocky's parents also hear</i>

14:01.840 --> 14:03.440
<i>the unmistakable cry…</i>

14:05.600 --> 14:07.080
…<i>of their little one.</i>

14:13.480 --> 14:17.600
<i>His voice has a unique signature</i>
<i>only his parents can identify.</i>

14:21.680 --> 14:23.200
<i>It's a family reunion.</i>

14:25.240 --> 14:27.240
<i>And two baby bellies</i>

14:28.280 --> 14:30.200
<i>are full at last.</i>

14:36.440 --> 14:40.160
<i>From the first stars</i>
<i>to the birth of our galaxy,</i>

14:40.240 --> 14:42.240
<i>Sun, and planet,</i>

14:43.480 --> 14:46.720
<i>gravity set the stage for life.</i>

14:53.800 --> 14:56.120
<i>But for Earth to become the home we know,</i>

14:57.840 --> 15:01.280
<i>gravity would need to send</i>
<i>a bit of chaos our way…</i>

15:07.320 --> 15:10.680
<i>…so evolution could run riot.</i>

15:20.200 --> 15:22.000
<i>Several months have passed.</i>

15:23.680 --> 15:25.800
<i>Rocky's now doubled in size…</i>

15:28.000 --> 15:29.400
<i>and is ready for love.</i>

15:30.920 --> 15:33.680
<i>But he won't truly be</i>
<i>an eligible bachelor…</i>

15:35.720 --> 15:39.080
<i>until he's become fit and handsome.</i>

15:43.320 --> 15:45.600
<i>First, a new outfit.</i>

15:50.680 --> 15:53.360
<i>Trading in his childish, fluffy feathers…</i>

15:55.880 --> 15:58.200
<i>for a shiny, waterproof coat…</i>

16:00.920 --> 16:02.880
<i>he's ready for his first swim.</i>

16:16.160 --> 16:17.960
<i>On the other end of the beach,</i>

16:19.760 --> 16:21.800
<i>Paloma is ready to launch as well.</i>

16:31.560 --> 16:34.800
<i>After only knowing dry land</i>
<i>their whole lives,</i>

16:36.080 --> 16:38.480
<i>it's an intimidating moment for both.</i>

16:43.000 --> 16:44.840
<i>Rocky thinks he's swimming…</i>

16:49.000 --> 16:51.760
<i>but Paloma actually is.</i>

17:03.480 --> 17:07.480
<i>Rocky finally figures out</i>
<i>he needs to be </i>in<i> the water.</i>

17:12.680 --> 17:16.360
<i>These young birds will be gone</i>
<i>for the next two years</i>…

17:18.960 --> 17:21.600
<i>on their own separate journeys.</i>

17:26.560 --> 17:29.080
<i>There are great riches</i>
<i>awaiting them in the ocean…</i>

17:32.320 --> 17:33.400
<i>thanks to gravity…</i>

17:36.360 --> 17:38.280
…<i>and our nearest neighbor.</i>

17:49.480 --> 17:51.760
<i>Not long after our planet formed…</i>

17:55.120 --> 17:57.640
<i>it collided with another young world.</i>

18:13.360 --> 18:15.200
<i>And out of the orbiting debris…</i>

18:20.960 --> 18:24.320
<i>…gravity formed</i>
<i>Earth's traveling companion…</i>

18:29.000 --> 18:29.840
<i>the Moon.</i>

18:36.680 --> 18:40.240
<i>The impact knocked</i>
<i>the young Earth onto its side…</i>

18:41.560 --> 18:44.040
-…<i>and threw it into turmoil…</i>

18:46.040 --> 18:48.800
<i>lurching and spinning wildly.</i>

18:52.280 --> 18:54.440
<i>But over billions of years,</i>

18:54.520 --> 18:58.320
<i>the gravitational tug</i>
<i>of the Moon tamed the Earth.</i>

18:59.640 --> 19:01.760
<i>The Moon drifted away.</i>

19:02.920 --> 19:05.000
<i>Earth's rotation slowed…</i>

19:07.400 --> 19:10.400
<i>which transformed Earth's story.</i>

19:15.200 --> 19:19.320
<i>Because slower spin meant longer days…</i>

19:22.000 --> 19:26.400
<i>and, therefore, more hours</i>
<i>of continuous sunshine</i>

19:26.480 --> 19:28.640
<i>penetrated the oceans…</i>

19:40.120 --> 19:45.400
…<i>creating the conditions</i>
<i>for the first life to get a foothold.</i>

19:52.000 --> 19:56.160
<i>The first step</i>
<i>in an underwater labyrinth of life</i>

19:57.000 --> 19:59.320
<i>that grew and grew…</i>

20:05.360 --> 20:10.160
<i>…eventually filling the oceans</i>
<i>with unimaginable wonders.</i>

20:24.560 --> 20:28.000
<i>Wonders that today provide</i>
<i>a rich ecosystem</i>

20:29.000 --> 20:31.520
<i>for two very hungry penguins…</i>

20:35.120 --> 20:37.320
<i>hundreds of kilometers apart</i>

20:38.000 --> 20:39.280
<i>in the open ocean.</i>

20:44.040 --> 20:47.400
<i>Paloma has reached the polar front…</i>

20:52.240 --> 20:56.520
<i>where the Southern Ocean</i>
<i>meets the warmer waters of the Atlantic,</i>

20:56.600 --> 20:59.600
<i>Pacific, and Indian Oceans.</i>

21:04.480 --> 21:08.160
<i>Here, nutrients are churned up from below,</i>

21:09.320 --> 21:11.720
<i>supporting thousands of species…</i>

21:17.000 --> 21:22.200
<i>including lantern fish,</i>
<i>a favorite of the king penguin.</i>

21:27.160 --> 21:29.040
<i>They live deep underwater.</i>

21:32.760 --> 21:34.760
<i>But that's no problem for Paloma.</i>

21:36.560 --> 21:40.400
<i>She's able to hunt</i>
<i>300 meters below the surface.</i>

22:02.840 --> 22:06.840
<i>Penguins are uniquely adapted</i>
<i>to dive and hunt at great depth.</i>

22:10.160 --> 22:14.320
<i>But to understand how</i>
<i>these remarkable adaptations came about,</i>

22:16.280 --> 22:21.080
<i>you need to know what gravity</i>
<i>had been up to 66 million years ago.</i>

22:31.680 --> 22:35.360
<i>In the cold outer reaches</i>
<i>of the solar system,</i>

22:36.040 --> 22:39.360
<i>millions of chunks</i>
<i>of ice and rock orbit the Sun.</i>

22:42.880 --> 22:45.680
<i>Most of the time,</i>
<i>these asteroids are no trouble.</i>

22:54.280 --> 22:56.800
<i>But sometimes they are.</i>

23:00.720 --> 23:03.560
<i>In the outer region of the asteroid belt,</i>

23:04.840 --> 23:08.600
<i>one particular rock,</i>
<i>ten kilometers across,</i>

23:09.360 --> 23:12.680
<i>was warmed by the Sun over millennia.</i>

23:16.880 --> 23:18.160
<i>And bit by bit,</i>

23:19.040 --> 23:25.200
<i>the warming began to shift this asteroid,</i>
<i>called Chicxulub, out of its orbit…</i>

23:28.120 --> 23:29.640
<i>until gravity took hold…</i>

23:32.000 --> 23:33.840
<i>pulling it in toward the Sun…</i>

23:38.040 --> 23:41.320
<i>sending it on</i>
<i>a collision course with Earth…</i>

23:48.160 --> 23:51.600
<i>…at 72,000 kilometers an hour.</i>

24:00.520 --> 24:04.840
<i>The impact triggered</i>
<i>a superheated wave of plasma…</i>

24:08.360 --> 24:12.360
<i>…causing wildfires and devastation</i>
<i>across the planet…</i>

24:15.160 --> 24:16.800
<i>blocking out the Sun.</i>

24:19.520 --> 24:23.080
<i>Three-quarters of Earth's species</i>
<i>were obliterated.</i>

24:25.680 --> 24:28.200
<i>It was bad news for the dinosaurs…</i>

24:30.200 --> 24:33.840
<i>but good news for the king penguin.</i>

24:39.840 --> 24:41.400
<i>Smaller and lighter,</i>

24:42.080 --> 24:44.720
<i>birds were able to survive the impact.</i>

24:46.920 --> 24:50.280
<i>They took to the skies and diversified.</i>

24:53.640 --> 24:55.640
<i>With large predators gone…</i>

24:58.360 --> 25:01.120
<i>the oceans abounded with fish.</i>

25:05.200 --> 25:09.120
<i>The penguin's ancestors</i>
<i>became expert divers,</i>

25:10.960 --> 25:12.240
<i>diving deeper</i>

25:13.360 --> 25:15.160
<i>and staying down longer</i>

25:16.720 --> 25:22.800
<i>until, ultimately, they lost</i>
<i>the ability to fly altogether.</i>

25:28.880 --> 25:30.960
<i>From soaring through the skies…</i>

25:34.880 --> 25:37.000
<i>to soaring through the oceans.</i>

25:42.680 --> 25:45.080
<i>Invaluable adaptations</i>

25:45.160 --> 25:48.800
<i>that Rocky and Paloma</i>
<i>have put to good use.</i>

25:53.800 --> 25:56.320
<i>Fitter and stronger,</i>

25:56.400 --> 25:59.760
<i>they are now ready to return</i>
<i>to their home shores</i>

25:59.840 --> 26:01.080
<i>in search of a mate.</i>

26:05.200 --> 26:07.480
<i>But their homecoming is interrupted…</i>

26:15.800 --> 26:16.720
<i>…by orcas,</i>

26:18.280 --> 26:21.080
<i>the only whale known to eat penguins.</i>

26:25.160 --> 26:27.880
<i>Paloma shifts into top gear.</i>

26:32.880 --> 26:35.400
<i>It will be a race to the finish.</i>

26:41.040 --> 26:42.320
<i>Orcas are fast.</i>

26:47.920 --> 26:50.480
<i>But king penguins are built for speed.</i>

27:12.800 --> 27:15.800
<i>Paloma is too quick for her pursuer.</i>

27:19.920 --> 27:24.280
<i>But Rocky took cover</i>
<i>in the kelp forests near the shore.</i>

27:38.680 --> 27:42.200
<i>And the hungry orca isn't going anywhere.</i>

28:00.080 --> 28:01.480
<i>Rocky sees his opening…</i>

28:06.280 --> 28:07.720
<i>and bolts for the shore.</i>

28:11.200 --> 28:14.280
<i>-He definitely knows how to swim now.</i>

28:20.000 --> 28:23.560
<i>Two long years roaming the sea,</i>

28:24.280 --> 28:27.400
<i>all for a chance</i>
<i>to enter the great lottery.</i>

28:29.120 --> 28:31.400
<i>The search for love.</i>

28:34.320 --> 28:38.760
<i>Gravity shaped the Sun, Earth, and Moon…</i>

28:41.400 --> 28:44.160
<i>creating a stable home</i>
<i>for life on our planet</i>

28:45.200 --> 28:48.480
<i>and steering evolution in new directions.</i>

28:56.680 --> 29:00.680
<i>But the ballad of Rocky and Paloma</i>
<i>needs one more part…</i>

29:03.200 --> 29:04.600
…<i>created by gravity</i>

29:06.240 --> 29:08.440
<i>in the fiery heart of the Sun.</i>

29:12.040 --> 29:12.920
<i>Light.</i>

29:17.240 --> 29:19.560
<i>Our star only shines because,</i>

29:19.640 --> 29:23.680
<i>at its center,</i>
<i>an intense battle is taking place.</i>

29:28.040 --> 29:29.720
<i>Gravity pulls inward…</i>

29:31.720 --> 29:35.200
<i>while intense pressure pushes back.</i>

29:41.800 --> 29:43.600
<i>This gravitational war….</i>

29:48.480 --> 29:51.640
…<i>causes atoms to collide and fuse…</i>

29:58.000 --> 30:00.400
<i>…releasing tiny pockets of energy…</i>

30:02.240 --> 30:05.080
<i>…in the form of photons…</i>

30:12.320 --> 30:15.880
<i>…that not only shower the Earth</i>
<i>with life-sustaining energy…</i>

30:18.240 --> 30:22.280
<i>but also bathe it in light.</i>

30:26.920 --> 30:29.960
<i>Light that contains</i>
<i>its own hidden wonders.</i>

30:33.000 --> 30:35.800
<i>Because within every sunbeam</i>

30:36.920 --> 30:38.040
<i>is a rainbow.</i>

30:41.400 --> 30:44.160
<i>Each photon has a unique wavelength</i>

30:45.440 --> 30:48.600
<i>and interacts with the stuff</i>
<i>our world is made of</i>

30:49.120 --> 30:50.320
<i>in a different way.</i>

31:01.880 --> 31:04.640
<i>Some wavelengths are absorbed.</i>

31:06.160 --> 31:08.680
<i>Others are reflected.</i>

31:12.760 --> 31:18.000
<i>How these light waves hit our eyes</i>
<i>determines what colors we see.</i>

31:22.400 --> 31:24.840
<i>And this ability to perceive color</i>

31:25.680 --> 31:29.680
<i>plays a key role</i>
<i>in the penguin dating game.</i>

31:39.200 --> 31:43.480
<i>Years of feasting at sea</i>
<i>have made Rocky fit and strong.</i>

31:48.120 --> 31:51.400
<i>Traits he needs to display</i>
<i>to attract a mate.</i>

31:58.200 --> 32:01.200
<i>Pigments that he synthesized himself</i>

32:02.360 --> 32:04.800
<i>color his feathers brilliant yellow…</i>

32:07.000 --> 32:09.480
<i>perfect for showing off his own flair</i>

32:11.360 --> 32:16.800
<i>and attracting the gaze</i>
<i>of the one bird in this crowd…</i>

32:22.000 --> 32:25.600
<i>-…who only has eyes for him.</i>

32:29.800 --> 32:30.640
<i>Paloma.</i>

32:44.520 --> 32:48.680
<i>Starlight reflects onto the retina</i>
<i>at the back of Paloma's eye.</i>

32:55.000 --> 32:58.280
<i>Here, millions of cone cells get to work</i>

32:58.360 --> 33:00.480
<i>decoding every wavelength…</i>

33:07.000 --> 33:12.200
<i>…which allows Paloma</i>
<i>to distinguish one color from another.</i>

33:16.480 --> 33:17.840
<i>In the blink of an eye,</i>

33:18.360 --> 33:22.600
<i>these lovebirds</i>
<i>are not only able to see their world</i>

33:23.640 --> 33:26.280
<i>but also understand it</i>

33:27.800 --> 33:30.280
<i>and find their soulmate.</i>

33:36.840 --> 33:40.840
<i>The courting then turns</i>
<i>to a carefully choreographed dance.</i>

33:43.680 --> 33:46.480
<i>Each displaying</i>
<i>their dazzling, yellow feathers…</i>

33:50.920 --> 33:52.280
<i>for the other to admire.</i>

34:03.600 --> 34:05.600
<i>Other suitors try their luck</i>

34:05.680 --> 34:07.000
<i>but to no avail.</i>

34:12.600 --> 34:14.360
<i>Because Rocky's yellow feathers</i>…

34:16.560 --> 34:18.360
<i>aren't his only selling point.</i>

34:22.240 --> 34:23.520
<i>By shaking his head…</i>

34:26.280 --> 34:28.280
<i>he encodes a secret message…</i>

34:30.680 --> 34:32.680
<i>in ultraviolet light.</i>

34:35.120 --> 34:37.240
<i>His beak catches the Sun</i>

34:39.000 --> 34:40.720
<i>and reflects its rays.</i>

34:47.200 --> 34:49.360
<i>And thanks to an extra cone cell…</i>

34:51.760 --> 34:56.640
<i>…Rocky and Paloma's eyes</i>
<i>can see colors beyond our own.</i>

34:58.240 --> 35:02.120
<i>These UV signals win Paloma over.</i>

35:04.040 --> 35:05.880
<i>They're the perfect match.</i>

35:12.840 --> 35:16.000
<i>Raising a penguin chick is a grueling task</i>

35:17.880 --> 35:21.480
<i>that requires both parents</i>
<i>to be in top form.</i>

35:26.320 --> 35:29.760
<i>Impressive yellow feathers</i>
<i>and a flashy beak</i>

35:29.840 --> 35:32.800
<i>are proof of strength and ability,</i>

35:34.320 --> 35:38.040
<i>essential characteristics</i>
<i>when it comes to bringing up a family.</i>

35:41.360 --> 35:44.120
<i>From all the thousands of other birds,</i>

35:45.000 --> 35:46.840
<i>Rocky and Paloma…</i>

35:49.640 --> 35:51.280
<i>have found each other.</i>

36:00.880 --> 36:03.480
<i>From the first ripples in the cosmic web…</i>

36:09.560 --> 36:11.240
…<i>to the birth of our Sun…</i>

36:13.680 --> 36:14.560
<i>planet,</i>

36:15.840 --> 36:16.720
<i>and Moon…</i>

36:21.680 --> 36:25.000
<i>…the impacts</i>
<i>that have written Earth's history…</i>

36:27.800 --> 36:33.160
<i>…to the force that powers the Sun,</i>
<i>painting our world in color…</i>

36:35.280 --> 36:40.280
<i>gravity has had a hand in all of it…</i>

36:44.200 --> 36:48.200
<i>guiding these two penguins</i>
<i>to their special moment</i>…

36:51.920 --> 36:54.080
<i>…on this special island…</i>

36:58.240 --> 37:02.120
<i>where it's not long</i>
<i>before something extra special</i>

37:02.200 --> 37:03.640
<i>is delivered to Earth.</i>

37:04.800 --> 37:09.760
<i>Rocky and Paloma are going</i>
<i>to be parents themselves.</i>

37:13.680 --> 37:15.440
<i>Ushering in a new life</i>

37:16.160 --> 37:19.080
<i>and maybe even new romance…</i>

37:21.880 --> 37:25.720
<i>with gravity, as ever,</i>
<i>helping to lead the way.</i>

37:33.880 --> 37:35.440
<i>All across the Earth,</i>

37:36.440 --> 37:38.880
<i>life is dazzling in its variety.</i>

38:04.520 --> 38:07.520
<i> It has taken 13.8 billion years</i>

38:07.600 --> 38:10.880
<i>to reach this one precious moment</i>

38:10.960 --> 38:13.680
<i>in time and space.</i>

38:22.520 --> 38:25.720
<i>Every animal made from the stars…</i>

38:27.720 --> 38:29.800
<i>synchronized with the planet,</i>

38:31.440 --> 38:34.720
<i>and sustained by gifts from the cosmos</i>

38:34.800 --> 38:38.400
<i>that only made it here by pure chance.</i>

38:52.320 --> 38:53.920
<i>All held in its place</i>

38:54.000 --> 38:55.120
<i>by the ultimate,</i>

38:56.040 --> 38:58.960
<i>the original force of attraction.</i>

39:07.320 --> 39:09.520
<i>The story of our universe</i>

39:09.600 --> 39:14.440
<i>is the story of how life came</i>
<i>to be here on this planet…</i>

39:17.880 --> 39:19.400
…<i>we call home.</i>

39:23.080 --> 39:27.120
<i>A story that is still being written.</i>
